To optimize this function, we can use bit manipulation techniques to count the number of '1' bits in the input. One such technique is called the Brian Kernighan's algorithm. 

The idea behind this algorithm is to keep toggling the least significant set bit of the input until it becomes zero. Whenever we toggle a set bit, we decrement a counter. The value of the counter at the end will be the number of '1' bits in the input.
